3#ifndef __NVKM_GPIO_PRIV_H__
4#define __NVKM_GPIO_PRIV_H__
5#define nvkm_gpio(p) container_of((p), struct nvkm_gpio, subdev)
6#include <subdev/gpio.h>
7
8struct nvkm_gpio_func {
9 int lines;
10
11 /* read and ack pending interrupts, returning only data
12 * for lines that have not been masked off, while still
13 * performing the ack for anything that was pending.
14 */
15 void (*intr_stat)(struct nvkm_gpio *, u32 *, u32 *);
16
17 /* mask on/off interrupts for hi/lo transitions on a
18 * given set of gpio lines
19 */
20 void (*intr_mask)(struct nvkm_gpio *, u32, u32, u32);
21
22 /* configure gpio direction and output value */
23 int (*drive)(struct nvkm_gpio *, int line, int dir, int out);
24
25 /* sense current state of given gpio line */
26 int (*sense)(struct nvkm_gpio *, int line);
27
28 /*XXX*/
29 void (*reset)(struct nvkm_gpio *, u8);
30};
31
32int nvkm_gpio_new_(const struct nvkm_gpio_func *, struct nvkm_device *,
33 int index, struct nvkm_gpio **);
34
35void nv50_gpio_reset(struct nvkm_gpio *, u8);
36int nv50_gpio_drive(struct nvkm_gpio *, int, int, int);
37int nv50_gpio_sense(struct nvkm_gpio *, int);
38
39void g94_gpio_intr_stat(struct nvkm_gpio *, u32 *, u32 *);
40void g94_gpio_intr_mask(struct nvkm_gpio *, u32, u32, u32);
41
42void gf119_gpio_reset(struct nvkm_gpio *, u8);
43int gf119_gpio_drive(struct nvkm_gpio *, int, int, int);
44int gf119_gpio_sense(struct nvkm_gpio *, int);
45#endif
